WEBVTT

00:03.380 --> 00:04.710
Previously
on "Grey's Anatomy"...

00:04.710 --> 00:06.000
Amelia: There's
a scientific study

00:06.000 --> 00:07.500
that if you stand like this
in superhero pose,

00:07.500 --> 00:08.830
you will perform
measurably better.

00:08.830 --> 00:10.250
Owen, will you marry me?

00:10.250 --> 00:11.710
-Where are we running?
-Ahh!

00:11.710 --> 00:13.710
Um, kids.

00:13.710 --> 00:14.750
-Five.
-Whoa. Five?!

00:14.750 --> 00:16.290
Hey, you got
a minute to talk?

00:16.290 --> 00:18.170
Amelia: Owen, there's
nothing to talk about.

00:18.170 --> 00:19.460
I don't want
to have a baby!

00:19.460 --> 00:21.960
Is she okay? Is she sober?
Just tell me that.

00:21.960 --> 00:23.290
Stephanie: She's safe.

00:23.290 --> 00:25.120
Tell her to come home.

00:30.380 --> 00:33.670
[ Breathes deeply ]

00:33.670 --> 00:35.580
[ Razor buzzes ]

00:35.580 --> 00:44.500
♪♪

00:44.500 --> 00:47.420
Amelia: There are 100 billion
neurons in the human brain...

00:47.420 --> 00:49.080
making and remaking
connections...

00:49.080 --> 00:53.920
♪ Today is sweet like honey ♪

00:53.920 --> 00:55.500
♪ Sugar in my step ♪
That's it?

00:55.500 --> 00:57.250
♪ With a pocket
full of sunny ♪

00:57.250 --> 00:59.880
Kinda makes you
look fierce.

00:59.880 --> 01:01.790
♪ Summer in my soul, and the
birds are sounding lovely ♪

01:01.790 --> 01:04.380
Are you sure you don't
want me to call your mom?

01:04.380 --> 01:06.380
No. She didn't come
for my wedding.

01:06.380 --> 01:08.040
She doesn't get to come
for my tumor.

01:08.040 --> 01:10.210
♪ We got the feeling ♪

01:10.210 --> 01:11.830
It's helping us with math...

01:11.830 --> 01:13.170
[ Door closes ]

01:13.170 --> 01:16.040
...remembering our keys,
our dad's voice --

01:16.040 --> 01:19.000
working hard all the time.

01:19.000 --> 01:22.460
♪ From my head down to my toes ♪

01:22.460 --> 01:25.500
♪ We got the feeling, ooh ♪

01:25.500 --> 01:27.000
♪ Got the feeling ♪

01:27.000 --> 01:28.750
♪ Ooh ♪

01:28.750 --> 01:31.080
♪ Got the feeling,
got the feeling ♪

01:31.080 --> 01:36.080
♪ Got, got the feeling, whoa ♪

01:36.080 --> 01:39.210
♪ Got the feeling,
got, got the feeling ♪

01:39.210 --> 01:43.460
So when the brain is faulty,
it's a big rewiring job.

01:43.460 --> 01:45.290
And there's no margin
for error.

01:45.290 --> 01:47.080
Koracick: I'll go in
through a subfrontal craniotomy,

01:47.080 --> 01:49.210
real clean,
small incision in the dura,

01:49.210 --> 01:50.750
and then scoop
the tumor out.

01:50.750 --> 01:52.620
I don't like the edema
around the tumor,

01:52.620 --> 01:54.710
but I got to dance with the girl
who brought me, so...

01:54.710 --> 01:57.580
[ Chuckles ]
I imagine you have questions.

01:57.580 --> 01:59.670
Yeah, uh, how many of these
have you done?

01:59.670 --> 02:02.000
So, so many.

02:02.000 --> 02:03.500
And what's
the recovery time?

02:03.500 --> 02:05.120
I took a 13-centimeter tumor
out of a cop

02:05.120 --> 02:06.460
in roughly the same place.

02:06.460 --> 02:08.210
He was walking day one,
talking day three,

02:08.210 --> 02:09.830
back at work
end of the week, so...

02:09.830 --> 02:11.250
Thank you, Tom.

02:11.250 --> 02:12.960
Yeah. See you
at the after party.

02:12.960 --> 02:16.540
[ Telephone rings ]

02:16.540 --> 02:18.500
He seems
arrogant enough.

02:18.500 --> 02:20.460
He's a showboat.

02:20.460 --> 02:22.250
And he works best under
pressure, so, DeLuca,

02:22.250 --> 02:24.750
ask him questions during
surgery, make him show off.

02:24.750 --> 02:27.330
And if I make it through --
When you make it through.

02:27.330 --> 02:29.170
-Early ambulation protocol.
-Thank you.

02:29.170 --> 02:30.790
Okay.
Meredith, if I die --

02:30.790 --> 02:32.290
You are not going to die.

02:32.290 --> 02:33.880
But if I do,
you call my mom.

02:33.880 --> 02:35.210
I'm sorry,
but she likes you.

02:35.210 --> 02:36.880
And, you, take my room.

02:36.880 --> 02:39.080
It is way better.
I kind of scammed you on that.

02:39.080 --> 02:40.620
Stop it.
No, she's right.
It's way better.

02:40.620 --> 02:41.880
Owen, if I'm gorked,

02:41.880 --> 02:44.210
do not overthink it,
do not visit me.

02:44.210 --> 02:45.830
just park me somewhere
and go on with your life.

02:45.830 --> 02:47.080
Amelia,
please cut it out.

02:47.080 --> 02:48.290
And if I need
unplugging,

02:48.290 --> 02:50.750
April has been named
my power of attorney.

02:50.750 --> 02:53.080
[ Chuckles ]

02:53.080 --> 02:54.790
W-Was I supposed
to say no?

02:54.790 --> 02:56.710
She likes me.
She will be there for you.

02:56.710 --> 02:59.040
But we're not so close
that she'll let emotion
dictate her decision.

03:03.000 --> 03:05.830
I don't know what's me and
what's tumor talking, but, um...

03:07.670 --> 03:10.170
[ Shakily ] In this moment,
I love you people tremendously.

03:10.170 --> 03:18.210
♪♪

03:18.210 --> 03:26.290
♪♪

03:26.290 --> 03:34.380
♪♪

03:34.380 --> 03:37.080
Koracick:
[ Softly ] I love this.

03:37.080 --> 03:40.170
[ Normal voice ] Are there
really studies on this?

03:40.170 --> 03:41.250
Yep.

03:41.250 --> 03:42.620
Yeah.

03:42.620 --> 03:46.040
♪♪

03:46.040 --> 03:49.500
When you're going into surgery,
you worry you won't wake up.

03:52.710 --> 03:56.420
But with brain surgery,
you worry you will wake up...

03:56.420 --> 04:05.500
♪♪

04:05.500 --> 04:07.500
...but you won't be there
when you do.

04:14.460 --> 04:15.880
[ Elevator bell dings ]
[ Sighs ]

04:15.880 --> 04:17.960
The first intern interview
is already here?

04:17.960 --> 04:20.250
Yes. 45 minutes early.

04:20.250 --> 04:21.830
We know they all have
the grades.

04:21.830 --> 04:23.460
We just need to see
if they're --

04:23.460 --> 04:24.880
Functional human beings.
[ Laughs ]

04:24.880 --> 04:26.540
You've worked very hard
for this. You deserve this.

04:26.540 --> 04:28.250
And even though
you overdosed your Aunt Joan

04:28.250 --> 04:29.290
on her blood-pressure
medication,

04:29.290 --> 04:31.210
you are awesome
because y-you can recite

04:31.210 --> 04:32.880
every artery in the body
alphabetically.

04:32.880 --> 04:34.080
[ Inhales sharply ]
Abdominal aorta,

04:34.080 --> 04:35.750
alveolar anterior,

04:35.750 --> 04:37.670
alveolar inferior,
alveolar superior...

04:37.670 --> 04:39.540
I think
we're finished here.

04:39.540 --> 04:41.540
[ Chuckling ] Next.
...anterior cecal.

04:41.540 --> 04:43.880
Megan: If you say
a number I don't like,

04:43.880 --> 04:46.120
I'm going to hit you
with this magazine.

04:46.120 --> 04:47.920
-Still over 100.
-Barely a fever.

04:47.920 --> 04:49.620
-A fever's a fever.
-It's minor.

04:49.620 --> 04:52.620
It's not like I'm having...
brain surgery or something.

04:52.620 --> 04:54.790
[ Scoffs ]

04:54.790 --> 04:57.210
She avoided you
during my surgery.
You're avoiding her now.

04:57.210 --> 04:59.080
I suddenly understand
your marriage completely.

04:59.080 --> 05:00.380
Amelia has
a lot of support.

05:00.380 --> 05:02.170
And with Riggs pulling
what he's pulled on you --

05:02.170 --> 05:03.460
I turned down
his proposal.

05:03.460 --> 05:05.210
I told him
I didn't want him.

05:05.210 --> 05:07.210
He had every right
and every reason

05:07.210 --> 05:10.460
to pack his bags
and walk away.

05:10.460 --> 05:13.500
I mean, a goodbye
might've been nice, but...

05:13.500 --> 05:15.120
Hmm.

05:15.120 --> 05:17.330
April: Please don't make me
have to unplug her.

05:17.330 --> 05:19.170
Please don't make me
have to unplug her.

05:19.170 --> 05:21.710
[ Inhales sharply ]
Lord, please make her be okay.

05:21.710 --> 05:24.790
[ The Beach Boys'
"Fun, Fun, Fun" plays ]
Please let her be okay.

05:24.790 --> 05:27.620
Please don't make me
have to unplug her.

05:27.620 --> 05:29.830
Koracick: ♪ And she'll
have fun, fun, fun ♪

05:29.830 --> 05:31.540
♪ Till her daddy
takes the T-bird away ♪

05:31.540 --> 05:33.330
♪ Fun, fun, fun till her daddy
takes the T-bird away ♪

05:33.330 --> 05:34.380
Any issues
with the edema?

05:34.380 --> 05:36.000
♪ Well, the girls
can't stand her ♪

05:36.000 --> 05:38.420
♪ 'Cause she walks, talks,
and drives like an ace now ♪

05:38.420 --> 05:40.670
Also wondering if you're
all the way around the dura.

05:40.670 --> 05:42.420
♪ She makes the Indy 500 ♪

05:42.420 --> 05:45.120
♪ Look like a Roman
chariot race, now ♪

05:45.120 --> 05:46.750
Also, why did you choose
this particular music?

05:46.750 --> 05:48.420
DeLuca, sing along
or shut up.

05:48.420 --> 05:50.080
♪ But she leads them
on a wild-goose chase now ♪

05:50.080 --> 05:52.500
♪ Goose chase now,
you drive like an ace ♪

05:52.500 --> 05:54.710
♪ And she'll have
fun, fun, fun ♪

05:54.710 --> 05:56.830
♪ Till her daddy
takes the T-bird away ♪

05:56.830 --> 05:58.830
♪ Fun, fun, fun
till her daddy takes... ♪

05:58.830 --> 06:00.330
I still can't believe --

06:00.330 --> 06:02.460
That masturbation
diagnosed a brain tumor?

06:02.460 --> 06:05.170
Yeah. God works
in such mysterious ways.

06:05.170 --> 06:06.580
[ Chuckles ]

06:06.580 --> 06:09.750
The Beach Boys seems like an
odd choice. Like, inappropriate.

06:09.750 --> 06:12.380
No, Riggs leaving Megan --
that's inappropriate.

06:12.380 --> 06:14.250
I never liked Riggs
in the first place.

06:14.250 --> 06:16.250
And I'm an excellent judge
of character.

06:16.250 --> 06:17.790
Right, because
you have zero history

06:17.790 --> 06:19.170
with crazy girlfriends.

06:19.170 --> 06:21.460
My judgment has improved
with age.

06:21.460 --> 06:23.250
♪ Well, you knew
all along that your dad ♪

06:23.250 --> 06:25.250
♪ Was gettin' wise
to you now ♪

06:25.250 --> 06:27.170
♪ You shouldn't have lied ♪

06:27.170 --> 06:29.790
♪ And since he took your set
of keys, you were thinking -- ♪

06:29.790 --> 06:31.250
♪ That your fun
is all through now ♪

06:31.250 --> 06:32.880
-Why did he stop singing?
-He stopped singing.

06:32.880 --> 06:34.880
♪ But you can
come along with me... ♪

06:34.880 --> 06:36.790
This is the crucial part.
He has to cut the last vessel.

06:36.790 --> 06:38.250
And sometimes
it's a feeder to the --

06:38.250 --> 06:39.540
[ Snip ]

06:39.540 --> 06:41.250
♪ And we'll have fun, fun, fun ♪
[ Gasps ]

06:41.250 --> 06:42.500
-What was that?
-What happened?

06:42.500 --> 06:44.040
That was the
vessel en passant.

06:44.040 --> 06:45.710
It looked like it was
going into the meningioma,

06:45.710 --> 06:47.580
but in fact it was going
straight through to the brain.

06:47.580 --> 06:50.120
He didn't have a choice.
It's okay.

06:50.120 --> 06:51.620
-Is it?
-It is?

06:51.620 --> 06:53.790
It's probably fine.
It could be really bad.

06:53.790 --> 06:55.960
-I'm sure it's fine.
-Hmm.

06:55.960 --> 06:58.790
♪ Fun, fun now that Daddy
took the T-bird away ♪

06:58.790 --> 07:00.460
♪ Whoo, whoo-ooh-ooh-ooh ♪

07:00.460 --> 07:01.830
♪ Fun, fun now that Daddy
took the T-bird away ♪

07:01.830 --> 07:03.710
Meredith: I'm saying
you clipped the vessel.

07:03.710 --> 07:05.500
Koracick: The tissue
went a little dusky. It
doesn't mean that that --

07:05.500 --> 07:06.620
Owen:
She's 11 hours post-op.

07:06.620 --> 07:08.620
Maggie:
Shouldn't she be awake by now?

07:08.620 --> 07:09.710
I'm not concerned yet.
With that amount of bleeding,

07:09.710 --> 07:11.710
recovery time can be --
She's awake.

07:11.710 --> 07:14.920
Thank, God. Thank you, God!
[ Inhales sharply ]

07:14.920 --> 07:17.210
Meredith: Amelia,
how do you feel?

07:17.210 --> 07:19.920
Amelia: I'm okay.
How'd it go?

07:19.920 --> 07:21.880
Amelia, can you hear me?
[ Fingers snapping ]

07:21.880 --> 07:23.830
Yes. I'm right here.

07:23.830 --> 07:25.620
Owen: Is she awake?

07:25.620 --> 07:27.920
Maggie: Or did she just
open her eyes? Amelia?

07:27.920 --> 07:29.460
They can't hear me.

07:29.460 --> 07:31.330
I don't think she's --
Oh, my God!

07:31.330 --> 07:33.710
L-Listen. Everybody's
recovery time is different.

07:33.710 --> 07:36.170
Let's not...panic.

07:36.170 --> 07:38.960
Oh, crap. Am I gorked?

07:40.500 --> 07:42.120
It's okay. She's okay.

07:42.120 --> 07:43.290
Oh, crap!

07:50.830 --> 07:52.710
[ Air hissing,
monitors beeping ]

07:58.170 --> 07:59.580
-Hey.
-Hmm!

07:59.580 --> 08:00.750
-Sorry.
-Hey.

08:00.750 --> 08:02.040
There's no change.

08:02.040 --> 08:03.750
But, uh, it's 5:30
in case you want

08:03.750 --> 08:05.380
to get a shower
or something.
Okay. Thanks.

08:07.670 --> 08:10.290
Ooh. Okay.

08:10.290 --> 08:12.540
I'm gonna go take
a shower, okay?

08:12.540 --> 08:14.540
I'll be back soon.

08:14.540 --> 08:17.000
Okay.
It's sweet you slept here.

08:17.000 --> 08:18.330
What?

08:18.330 --> 08:20.380
I think she just
squeezed my hand.

08:20.380 --> 08:22.210
Amelia, did you
just squeeze my hand?

08:22.210 --> 08:24.880
Ow. Stop talking.

08:24.880 --> 08:26.580
My head hurts, Meredith.

08:26.580 --> 08:28.170
I'm trying to sleep.

08:28.170 --> 08:29.580
-Maybe not.
-[ Coughs ]

08:29.580 --> 08:31.750
Oh, my God.
She's breathing over the tube.

08:31.750 --> 08:34.120
-Let's get her extubated.
-Okay. This is good!

08:34.120 --> 08:35.210
This is good.

08:35.210 --> 08:38.580
Ow. God.
So much talking.

08:40.040 --> 08:42.540
I know that I'm younger
than most of your applicants,

08:42.540 --> 08:44.750
so to answer some questions
you may have,

08:44.750 --> 08:47.960
I went to high school at 12,
I went to college at 14,

08:47.960 --> 08:49.620
I went to medical school
at 16,

08:49.620 --> 08:51.420
and I lost
my virginity at 18.

08:53.210 --> 08:55.170
You may not have asked
that last one.

08:57.420 --> 08:59.790
Have to keep this on
in case Mass Gen calls.

08:59.790 --> 09:01.120
They're my number one.

09:01.120 --> 09:02.920
But you guys are
a solid number two.

09:02.920 --> 09:05.540
[ Cellphone chimes ]

09:05.540 --> 09:07.080
You know what, though?

09:07.080 --> 09:10.120
I think after being here,
I'm impressed.

09:10.120 --> 09:11.790
Grey-Sloan
is moving up.

09:11.790 --> 09:15.170
Level one trauma.
The weather's amazing.

09:17.000 --> 09:18.960
[ Indistinct chatter ]

09:18.960 --> 09:21.920
[ Telephone rings ]

09:21.920 --> 09:23.580
Richard: Ahh.
How was the flight?

09:23.580 --> 09:24.670
Fine.

09:24.670 --> 09:26.670
-Ah. And the service?
-It was tasteful.

09:26.670 --> 09:28.920
It was a bunch of kiss-asses
sniffing around for money,

09:28.920 --> 09:30.460
telling stories
about how Harper Avery

09:30.460 --> 09:32.460
was nice and decent
and [Scoffs] respected women.

09:32.460 --> 09:34.540
All right, so,
we'll have a family supper

09:34.540 --> 09:36.920
and do our own thing and talk
about the real Harper Avery.

09:36.920 --> 09:39.380
Right now I need to change.
Want to help me?

09:41.040 --> 09:42.170
Koracick:
Catherine Avery?

09:43.250 --> 09:46.210
Thomas Koracick?!
[ Both laugh ]

09:46.210 --> 09:48.580
Ohh! How is it that
I'm aging and you aren't?

09:48.580 --> 09:50.500
-Oh, shut up.
-[ Clears throat ]

09:50.500 --> 09:52.880
Uh, you've met my husband,
Richard Webber.

09:52.880 --> 09:55.170
-Oh!
-And this my son, Jackson.

09:55.170 --> 09:57.380
-Oh! H-How old is he?
-Hey.

09:57.380 --> 09:59.420
Why?
I want to make sure
he's not mine.

09:59.420 --> 10:01.500
-You are just awful.
-[ Chuckles ]

10:01.500 --> 10:03.210
Uh, how's, uh, Shepherd?

10:03.210 --> 10:06.290
She's, uh, responsive,
not yet verbal.

10:06.290 --> 10:07.710
It's early.

10:07.710 --> 10:09.040
We should catch up.

10:09.040 --> 10:11.880
[ Chuckles ]

10:11.880 --> 10:13.500
Anything you want
to tell me?

10:14.920 --> 10:17.170
I prefer
to let you wonder,

10:17.170 --> 10:18.830
keep the mystery alive.

10:18.830 --> 10:19.790
Richard: Mm-hmm.

10:19.790 --> 10:21.920
Mmm. [ Laughs ]

10:21.920 --> 10:25.380
Ooh! Look at
Dr. Fancypants!

10:25.380 --> 10:27.830
Trying to lure
in that big facelift money?

10:27.830 --> 10:29.960
I was at a funeral.

10:30.880 --> 10:33.380
I am a terrible person.

10:33.380 --> 10:34.960
You look very somber.

10:39.420 --> 10:40.790
How much money
did he leave you?

10:40.790 --> 10:42.330
That's not
an appropriate question.

10:42.330 --> 10:44.040
Well, I just want
to know exactly.

10:44.040 --> 10:46.710
I mean, do they just back up
a truckload of silver spoons?

10:46.710 --> 10:47.960
[ Chuckles ]

10:47.960 --> 10:49.880
It's a fleet of limos,
not a truck.

10:49.880 --> 10:52.080
Um, you, uh, paged me?
What's up?

10:52.080 --> 10:54.380
[ Sighs ] Bad timing.
Never mind.

10:54.380 --> 10:56.120
What do you mean?
Bad timing for what?

10:57.500 --> 10:59.460
What?

10:59.460 --> 11:01.540
I'm publishing
Megan Hunt's surgery,

11:01.540 --> 11:04.120
and it might get consideration
for a Harper Avery.

11:05.500 --> 11:08.790
So you want
to take my name off it.

11:08.790 --> 11:11.040
No, I understand --
You can't win a Harper Avery

11:11.040 --> 11:13.500
if the article says
"Jackson Avery."

11:13.500 --> 11:16.620
I mean, I know the timing
of the ask is unfortunate,

11:16.620 --> 11:18.460
but the deadline
is in a few days.

11:18.460 --> 11:21.120
And...I really am sorry
for your loss.

11:23.080 --> 11:24.830
-Take my name off, then.
-Yeah?

11:24.830 --> 11:26.670
Go for it.
Yeah, just be grateful

11:26.670 --> 11:29.170
that your mother didn't
start up a foundation.

11:29.170 --> 11:31.380
Yeah, that Alzheimer's
really put a wrench

11:31.380 --> 11:33.920
in her charitable giving,
but I owe you one.

11:33.920 --> 11:35.250
-Thanks.
-Yes, you do.

11:37.000 --> 11:38.170
Here we go.
[ Groans ]

11:38.170 --> 11:39.330
Just a little bit more.

11:39.330 --> 11:41.420
[ Yells ]

11:41.420 --> 11:43.170
Please stop.

11:43.170 --> 11:44.960
[ Sobs ]
No! It hurts!

11:44.960 --> 11:46.880
[ Yells ]

11:46.880 --> 11:48.960
DeLuca, what the hell
are you doing?!

11:48.960 --> 11:51.290
It's early ambulation.
Dr. Shepherd does it
with all her patients.

11:51.290 --> 11:53.000
This patient
is post-op day one.

11:53.000 --> 11:54.250
Put her back in that bed.

11:54.250 --> 11:55.500
She told me to do this.

11:55.500 --> 11:57.330
I change my mind.
I change my mind.

11:57.330 --> 12:00.170
No. The giant tumor that was
pressing on her frontal lobe

12:00.170 --> 12:02.120
told you to do it.
It also made me promise

12:02.120 --> 12:04.830
not to give her any opioids,
which is so incredibly stupid.

12:04.830 --> 12:07.620
Put her back
in this bed now!

12:07.620 --> 12:09.080
Agreed. DeLuca, I agree.

12:09.080 --> 12:11.000
-Sir, she made me promise.
-Damn it!

12:11.000 --> 12:13.120
[ Chuckles ] Hey.
You sleeping with her?

12:13.120 --> 12:15.290
-What?
-What?!

12:15.290 --> 12:16.880
You heard me. You getting
some extra office hours
in with Shepherd?

12:16.880 --> 12:18.880
No! Okay? Just --
I-It's her protocol.

12:18.880 --> 12:20.790
And her patients have
a high recovery rate --

12:20.790 --> 12:22.830
higher than yours, which
she wanted me to say to you,

12:22.830 --> 12:25.210
because she knew
you wouldn't like this.

12:25.210 --> 12:26.830
[ Amelia groans ]

12:26.830 --> 12:28.250
I am such an ass.

12:28.250 --> 12:31.790
If her intracranial pressure
increases, it's on you.

12:35.040 --> 12:36.380
Okay, Dr. Shepherd.

12:36.380 --> 12:38.790
You got this, okay?
Just to the chair.

12:38.790 --> 12:40.830
I mean, we could. It's
probably effective, but I'm --

12:40.830 --> 12:44.080
[ Screams ]

12:44.080 --> 12:46.880
[ Exhales sharply ]
I just want to see my kid.

12:46.880 --> 12:49.620
I'll take oral antibiotics.
It's just a low-grade fever.

12:52.080 --> 12:54.710
No. Unfortunately,
it's more than that.

12:54.710 --> 12:56.380
Your white count
is elevated.

12:56.380 --> 12:59.120
There's some erythema.
[ Sighs ]

12:59.120 --> 13:01.500
We're gonna need to do
three days IV of cefazolin.

13:01.500 --> 13:03.000
Three days?

13:03.000 --> 13:05.790
-I'm sorry.
-[ Groans ]

13:05.790 --> 13:08.960
[ Exhales deeply ]

13:08.960 --> 13:10.540
Have you heard
from Nathan?

13:10.540 --> 13:12.750
-No. Have you?
-No.

13:12.750 --> 13:14.750
For what it's worth, I told him
you were the real deal.

13:14.750 --> 13:16.580
I sent him to you.

13:16.580 --> 13:20.170
And I sent him to you.
Pretty firmly.

13:23.540 --> 13:26.120
[ Laughs ]

13:26.120 --> 13:27.790
I think we broke
his brain.

13:27.790 --> 13:29.880
[ Both laugh ]

13:29.880 --> 13:32.170
[ Woman on P.A.
speaking indistinctly ]

13:32.170 --> 13:35.080
Hey, Wilson,
Megan's got cellulitis,

13:35.080 --> 13:37.210
so let's start her
on one gram "Q,"

13:37.210 --> 13:39.540
8 of cefazolin, and
increase her fluids please.

13:39.540 --> 13:41.210
W-W-Wait. This won't affect
your article, will it?

13:43.380 --> 13:47.040
No. I-I'm only asking because
I'm worried about you...

13:48.460 --> 13:51.710
and her and...medicine.

13:51.710 --> 13:53.830
Yes, Wilson -- I'm putting
your name on the article.

13:53.830 --> 13:55.960
[ Laughing ] Really? Oh, my God.
Okay, thank you.

13:55.960 --> 13:58.330
Thank you.
[ Clears throat ]

13:58.330 --> 14:00.790
Oh, and the journal is
asking for photos of us

14:00.790 --> 14:02.380
to put with the article,

14:02.380 --> 14:04.120
so if you have one you like,
just send it to me.

14:04.120 --> 14:05.790
Okay.

14:05.790 --> 14:11.500
♪♪

14:11.500 --> 14:15.420
In, out, out, out --
Ow, ow.

14:15.420 --> 14:19.330
Amelia, the body
can't heal as quickly

14:19.330 --> 14:21.670
if it's experiencing
so much pain.

14:21.670 --> 14:23.420
[ Breathes heavily, moans ]

14:23.420 --> 14:26.330
AA has no opinion on drugs
for pain relief

14:26.330 --> 14:28.790
as long as you follow
the doctor's orders.

14:28.790 --> 14:31.040
Opioids are
my drug of choice.

14:31.040 --> 14:33.420
What if they told you you could
have "just a drink or two"

14:33.420 --> 14:35.420
if the doctor says it's okay?

14:35.420 --> 14:37.080
You're sure you don't
want to reconsider?

14:38.750 --> 14:40.170
Please stop.

14:40.170 --> 14:42.540
I didn't think so.

14:42.540 --> 14:43.750
But I had to ask.

14:43.750 --> 14:47.380
[ Monitor beeping ]

14:47.380 --> 14:49.120
[ Sobs ]

14:58.290 --> 15:00.210
I used to scream at her
to shut up

15:00.210 --> 15:01.710
all the time in my head.

15:01.710 --> 15:03.540
No, no. I heard you
a couple times.

15:03.540 --> 15:05.330
I mean, now I wish
she would just say anything.

15:05.330 --> 15:07.040
-How is she?
-Is she talking?

15:07.040 --> 15:08.420
-No.
-Did you call her mom yet?

15:08.420 --> 15:11.750
Did you unplug her yet?
[ Laughter ]

15:11.750 --> 15:14.290
That's not funny.
At all.

15:14.290 --> 15:16.620
I mean, seriously, so,
she left a thriving practice

15:16.620 --> 15:18.920
and a fiancé in L.A. to come
and live with her brother

15:18.920 --> 15:20.710
who she resented.
Yeah?

15:20.710 --> 15:21.750
That was the tumor.

15:21.750 --> 15:23.290
Wow.
How did we miss this?

15:23.290 --> 15:25.120
Man, I just wish I had a tumor
to blame my stupid crap on.

15:25.120 --> 15:27.170
No. Guys!
[ Laughter ]

15:27.170 --> 15:29.210
"DeLuca, I'm sorry
I hit you. Tumor."

15:29.210 --> 15:31.170
[ Laughter ]
-This is not cool.
-Riggs. Tumor.

15:31.170 --> 15:32.170
-Minnick.
-Oh, tumor.

15:32.170 --> 15:34.040
No!
Do not encourage them.

15:34.040 --> 15:36.500
What?
You have to laugh, April.

15:36.500 --> 15:38.330
I mean, in situations like this,
you have to laugh.

15:38.330 --> 15:40.210
No. She trusted me
with her life.

15:40.210 --> 15:42.620
-All: Tumor!
-[ Laughing ] Stop!

15:42.620 --> 15:44.620
[ Cellphone rings ]

15:44.620 --> 15:46.040
Speak of the devil.

15:46.040 --> 15:47.960
-My tumor's calling.
-Oh, are you gonna answer?

15:47.960 --> 15:50.380
No. Once that's diagnosed,
you cut it right out.

15:50.380 --> 15:52.210
Hey, Riggs panicked.
People panic.

15:52.210 --> 15:54.290
Oh, don't defend him.
[ Cellphone chimes ]

15:54.290 --> 15:55.960
-It's DeLuca.
-Amelia's talking!

15:55.960 --> 15:57.290
-She's talking.
-Really?!

16:00.170 --> 16:02.580
-She's talking?
-Sort of.

16:02.580 --> 16:03.920
[ Amelia speaking French ]

16:03.920 --> 16:05.580
It's weird, right?

16:05.580 --> 16:08.080
[ Speaks French ]

16:08.080 --> 16:09.580
-It's French.
-She speaks French?

16:09.580 --> 16:11.500
[ Speaks French ]
I speak French.
She speaks German.

16:11.500 --> 16:13.040
-What is she saying?
-[ Speaks French ]

16:13.040 --> 16:15.040
Sorry. She said she needs
a glass of water.

16:15.040 --> 16:16.290
Oh.

16:16.290 --> 16:17.960
You know,
all the Shepherd children

16:17.960 --> 16:19.380
went to
French preschool.

16:19.380 --> 16:21.250
And it's still
in her brain somewhere?

16:21.250 --> 16:23.330
-Merci.
-I've seen this before.

16:23.330 --> 16:25.290
It reverses on its own,
but this is --

16:25.290 --> 16:26.750
It's still good.
It's progress.

16:26.750 --> 16:28.210
Amelia.

16:28.210 --> 16:30.580
[ Speaks French ]

16:30.580 --> 16:34.380
[ Speaking French ]

16:34.380 --> 16:35.920
What'd she say?

16:35.920 --> 16:38.330
Uh, I asked her
if she could speak in English,

16:38.330 --> 16:41.040
and she said, "Didn't even know
I could speak French."

16:41.040 --> 16:42.120
[ Chuckles softly ]

16:43.670 --> 16:47.210
Weaknesses? Uh, hmm.

16:47.210 --> 16:51.290
I hate all my peers.
All of them.

16:51.290 --> 16:53.420
Yeah, med school is filled
with legacy kids

16:53.420 --> 16:56.040
who expect
everything easy.

16:56.040 --> 16:58.250
I had to work my ass off
for everything that I have.

16:58.250 --> 16:59.960
I saw what I wanted,
I took dead aim,

16:59.960 --> 17:01.380
and I earned it.

17:01.380 --> 17:03.420
But if that attitude
is a problem,

17:03.420 --> 17:05.420
you definitely
shouldn't hire me.

17:07.500 --> 17:09.670
You'll get a major
signal boost from me.

17:09.670 --> 17:11.040
When I started med school,

17:11.040 --> 17:13.040
I had 47 followers
on Instagram.

17:13.040 --> 17:16.080
That number's
over 10,000 now.

17:16.080 --> 17:18.120
People are really invested
in my journey.

17:18.120 --> 17:21.420
And when I'm here,
that'll become our journey.

17:21.420 --> 17:23.790
Oh! Which reminds me --
Can we get a Snap?

17:23.790 --> 17:25.580
[ Phone unlocks ]

17:25.580 --> 17:26.920
One...
[ Camera shutter clicks ]

17:26.920 --> 17:29.620
[ Indistinct conversations ]

17:29.620 --> 17:32.500
Woman on P.A.:
Dr. Steve Irvan to the O.R.

17:32.500 --> 17:35.000
Dr. Steve Irvan to the O.R.

17:35.000 --> 17:36.960
[ Indistinct conversations ]

17:36.960 --> 17:39.210
[ Telephone rings ]

17:39.210 --> 17:41.170
[ Snoring ]

17:43.620 --> 17:45.040
[ Chuckles ]

17:47.540 --> 17:49.080
You're overreacting.

17:49.080 --> 17:50.960
I-I have to get this out!

17:50.960 --> 17:52.960
No! Megan, you're in the middle
of an antibiotic treatment.

17:52.960 --> 17:54.170
You can't just --
Megan, stop!

17:54.170 --> 17:55.540
[ Rapid beeping ]
What's happening?

17:55.540 --> 17:57.250
Farouk's at the hospital
in Baghdad,

17:57.250 --> 17:58.540
and I can't get him
on the phone,

17:58.540 --> 18:00.080
and my C.O. can't tell me
what's going on.

18:00.080 --> 18:01.790
-They said he was anemic.
-He's not anemic.

18:01.790 --> 18:03.880
He eats dates every day,
which is plenty of iron.

18:03.880 --> 18:05.500
Look. I have to go.

18:05.500 --> 18:07.040
You can just write me
a prescription for the rest,

18:07.040 --> 18:08.380
and I'll fill it on the way
to the airport.

18:08.380 --> 18:09.880
Megan, you're bleeding.
Give me your arm.

18:09.880 --> 18:12.080
And you have an infection,
and you know what that means.

18:12.080 --> 18:13.380
I'll sign
an A.M.A. form, okay?!

18:13.380 --> 18:15.170
When I was adopting my daughter,
there was a moment

18:15.170 --> 18:17.380
where I thought they
were gonna take her
from me, so I stole her.

18:17.380 --> 18:19.420
I kidnapped my own daughter

18:19.420 --> 18:22.290
because I felt exactly
the way you feel right now.

18:22.290 --> 18:24.040
All I did was make
everything worse.

18:24.040 --> 18:26.290
I made it worse for her,
and I made it worse for me.

18:26.290 --> 18:29.330
So let's just
take a moment, okay?

18:29.330 --> 18:31.330
[ Breathing sharply ]

18:31.330 --> 18:33.080
You can't help him
if you're dead.

18:33.080 --> 18:38.080
♪♪

18:38.080 --> 18:41.540
[ Siren wailing ]

18:41.540 --> 18:43.670
Hey.

18:43.670 --> 18:45.540
You okay?

18:45.540 --> 18:47.170
[ Sighs ]

18:47.170 --> 18:49.380
I don't have Harriet
tonight.

18:49.380 --> 18:52.120
I have trouble going home
when I don't have Harriet.

18:52.120 --> 18:54.540
[ Exhales deeply ]

18:54.540 --> 18:56.210
I remember that.

18:56.210 --> 18:59.120
[ Chair wheels roll ]

18:59.120 --> 19:02.250
It's really hard.
At first.

19:02.250 --> 19:03.710
At first?

19:03.710 --> 19:06.500
Yeah. Eventually...

19:06.500 --> 19:08.500
you have a new normal.

19:08.500 --> 19:09.830
You know,
eventually, you --

19:09.830 --> 19:11.880
You miss her on the nights
that you don't have her,

19:11.880 --> 19:14.460
but you know that she's
somewhere safe and loved,

19:14.460 --> 19:17.420
and the ache
is just less.

19:17.420 --> 19:19.790
And then maybe
some new grown-up fun

19:19.790 --> 19:22.080
comes into your life.
[ Scoffs ]

19:22.080 --> 19:24.960
And maybe there's
some joy in that.

19:24.960 --> 19:28.330
I don't want a new normal.

19:28.330 --> 19:32.460
♪♪

19:32.460 --> 19:33.710
[ Sighs ]

19:33.710 --> 19:40.120
♪♪

19:40.120 --> 19:43.040
Don't you have hot Italian sex
waiting for you?

19:43.040 --> 19:45.170
[ Exhales deeply ]
I do.

19:45.170 --> 19:47.620
-[ Laughs ] You do.
-Mm-hmm.

19:47.620 --> 19:49.540
[ Chuckles ]

19:51.790 --> 19:53.330
Hey. How is she?

19:53.330 --> 19:54.920
The same.

19:54.920 --> 19:56.500
[ Exhales sharply ]
Meredith, what do you think?

19:56.500 --> 19:58.170
I mean, how bad is this
long term?

19:58.170 --> 19:59.500
Do you think
we'll get her back?

19:59.500 --> 20:00.670
[ Cellphone vibrates ]

20:00.670 --> 20:02.500
I wish I knew.

20:02.500 --> 20:04.250
Amelia: [ Sleepily ]
Would you keep it down?

20:04.250 --> 20:06.000
-Sorry.
-That was English!

20:06.000 --> 20:08.750
-Wait.
-She spoke English.

20:08.750 --> 20:10.420
When was I not?

20:10.420 --> 20:12.920
How are you?
How do you feel?

20:12.920 --> 20:15.170
I'm okay. I'm good.

20:15.170 --> 20:17.540
Do you know what happened?
Do you know where you are?

20:19.460 --> 20:23.330
I had a surgery.
I had a brain tumor.

20:23.330 --> 20:24.880
-Call Koracick.
-Mm-hmm.

20:24.880 --> 20:27.500
Ugh. No. Koracick
is such a blowhard.

20:27.500 --> 20:29.540
-[ Chuckles ]
-This is good!

20:29.540 --> 20:30.960
You should call Derek.

20:33.920 --> 20:35.960
What?

20:46.210 --> 20:48.330
Amelia: I mean, I know
that Derek is dead.

20:48.330 --> 20:50.330
I just forget he was dead.

20:50.330 --> 20:52.330
But then the second that you
tell me, it's all there.

20:52.330 --> 20:54.080
It's like I have
this jigsaw puzzle,

20:54.080 --> 20:56.380
but I can't put the pieces in
until you give them to me.

20:56.380 --> 20:57.830
What if I can't be
a surgeon anymore?

20:57.830 --> 20:59.620
What if I get into surgery and
I can't find my way back out?

20:59.620 --> 21:01.460
She's panicking.

21:01.460 --> 21:04.500
Amelia, work the problem.

21:04.500 --> 21:07.710
What's the cause
of your memory loss?

21:07.710 --> 21:10.580
It's, uh,
retrograde amnesia.

21:10.580 --> 21:12.210
From?

21:12.210 --> 21:13.750
From damage
to the temporal lobe.

21:13.750 --> 21:16.250
But you were in the frontal.

21:16.250 --> 21:18.380
There could be
interruption of blood flow,

21:18.380 --> 21:21.080
ischemia-reperfusion injury,
edema.

21:21.080 --> 21:22.710
It's likely temporary.

21:22.710 --> 21:24.120
W-- Say that again.

21:28.880 --> 21:30.420
It might be temporary.

21:30.420 --> 21:34.000
Yes. It will be.
You know what this is.

21:34.000 --> 21:35.790
You don't have to
be afraid of it.

21:35.790 --> 21:39.460
You will be
a surgeon again.

21:39.460 --> 21:41.290
You're too good not to.

21:41.290 --> 21:42.830
So am I.

21:42.830 --> 21:45.170
Now, I need you
to simmer down

21:45.170 --> 21:47.790
so I can get
these scans, okay?

21:50.000 --> 21:52.670
-Okay.
-Thank you.

21:52.670 --> 21:55.710
She was hot for teacher back in
the day. She tell you about me?

21:55.710 --> 21:57.750
[ Cellphone ringing ]

21:59.460 --> 22:01.420
[ Cellphone slides ]

22:01.420 --> 22:03.830
[ Cellphone unlocks ]
Stop calling me.

22:03.830 --> 22:06.210
If you couldn't think of
anything to say before you left,

22:06.210 --> 22:08.620
there certainly isn't
anything to talk about now.

22:08.620 --> 22:10.040
Nathan: Hello, Dr. Grey.

22:10.040 --> 22:12.460
I'm so glad I was
finally able to reach you.

22:12.460 --> 22:14.290
Putting you on
speakerphone, okay?

22:14.290 --> 22:16.170
Okay.

22:16.170 --> 22:17.620
I'm here at the embassy
in Baghdad,

22:17.620 --> 22:19.170
and the officials
have some questions

22:19.170 --> 22:21.540
they need answered
by Farouk Shami's doctor

22:21.540 --> 22:23.670
regarding
his beta-thalassemia

22:23.670 --> 22:25.580
and the clinical trial
you're running.

22:25.580 --> 22:28.750
So we can secure his
medical travel visa, okay?

22:28.750 --> 22:30.380
Y-Yes, of course,
Dr. Riggs.

22:30.380 --> 22:33.040
I'm sorry I didn't
call you back sooner.

22:33.040 --> 22:35.210
Dr. Alazari: Hello, Dr. Grey.
I'm Dr. Alazari,

22:35.210 --> 22:38.380
the U.S. Embassy
Panel Physician.
Of course.

22:38.380 --> 22:40.500
In the sample you received,
how was his MCV?

22:40.500 --> 22:42.000
[ Mouse clicking ]

22:42.000 --> 22:43.960
Uh, low -- 68.

22:43.960 --> 22:45.540
Ferritin level?

22:45.540 --> 22:49.210
Uh, 111, but the sample could've
decayed during transport.

22:49.210 --> 22:51.580
Were there any Heinz bodies
on the peripheral blood smear?

22:51.580 --> 22:53.710
Um, I'm sorry.
I'm having trouble hearing you.

22:53.710 --> 22:56.580
Let me move
to a better spot.
[ Keys clacking ]

22:56.580 --> 22:58.960
Dr. Grey, I said, "Were there
any Heinz bodies --"

22:58.960 --> 23:01.120
Yes. There were Heinz bodies
on the blood smear.

23:01.120 --> 23:03.080
Thank you, Doctor.
We will let you know

23:03.080 --> 23:04.620
if we have
any further questions.

23:04.620 --> 23:07.500
Okay. Great. Thanks.

23:07.500 --> 23:08.960
Dr. Riggs?

23:08.960 --> 23:10.830
[ Static ]

23:10.830 --> 23:12.040
Hello?

23:12.040 --> 23:13.670
Nathan:
I'm alone now.

23:13.670 --> 23:15.580
Why didn't you tell me
you were gonna do this?!

23:15.580 --> 23:16.920
Why didn't you
pick up your phone?!

23:16.920 --> 23:18.330
I've been calling you
for days!

23:18.330 --> 23:19.830
Why didn't you call
someone else?!

23:19.830 --> 23:22.040
Because they are
rule followers, Meredith,

23:22.040 --> 23:24.080
and you're the one that told me
to make the grand gesture.

23:24.080 --> 23:26.210
I'm sorry.
When you left, I just --

23:26.210 --> 23:28.580
I didn't know.
Do you think it worked?

23:28.580 --> 23:30.580
I don't know. Look.
If we're back in Seattle

23:30.580 --> 23:32.170
by 3:00 tomorrow,
then it worked.

23:32.170 --> 23:33.500
Okay.
So what can I do now?

23:33.500 --> 23:35.420
Just don't tell Megan
about this, okay?

23:35.420 --> 23:37.000
Not until I know for sure
what's gonna happen.

23:37.000 --> 23:39.380
Pick up your phone
next time!
[ Click ]

23:39.380 --> 23:42.000
[ Cellphone locks ]

23:42.000 --> 23:43.580
[ Softly ] I just
want to help people,

23:43.580 --> 23:46.170
and I think that
doctors can save lives

23:46.170 --> 23:49.580
and change the world
and eradicate diseases.

23:49.580 --> 23:50.880
I-I'm sorry.

23:50.880 --> 23:54.170
Um, can you just speak up
a little bit?

23:54.170 --> 23:57.710
Um, I just want
to help people,

23:57.710 --> 24:01.040
and I think that doctors
can change the world,

24:01.040 --> 24:03.580
help save lives,
and eradicate disease.

24:03.580 --> 24:06.710
[ Chuckles, sighs ]

24:06.710 --> 24:08.460
[ Sighs ]

24:08.460 --> 24:10.960
There was a problem,

24:10.960 --> 24:12.670
and the problem
has been addressed.

24:14.420 --> 24:16.120
Sports band!
[ Chuckles ]

24:16.120 --> 24:18.500
I tried contacts,
but they required me

24:18.500 --> 24:22.830
to touch my eyeball
with my finger, so...no.

24:22.830 --> 24:27.170
♪♪

24:27.170 --> 24:29.420
Catherine:
Hello, there!

24:29.420 --> 24:31.580
Hi.

24:31.580 --> 24:33.750
-Maggie?
-[ Chuckles ]

24:33.750 --> 24:36.460
Ohh!
I wasn't expecting you.

24:36.460 --> 24:38.120
Well, you know,
I saw her on the way out,

24:38.120 --> 24:40.620
and I -- I thought
we could set another place.

24:40.620 --> 24:42.460
Uh-huh.
[ Chuckles ]

24:42.460 --> 24:45.120
-Oh. Hey.
-Hey.

24:46.170 --> 24:48.040
That looks amazing.

24:48.040 --> 24:51.540
Yes. Well, welcome.
Welcome.

24:51.540 --> 24:53.580
Richard,
could you help me

24:53.580 --> 24:55.250
in the kitchen
for a moment, please?

24:55.250 --> 24:57.710
Excuse me.
[ Claps hands ]

24:57.710 --> 24:59.120
[ Chuckles ]

25:03.750 --> 25:06.880
I said family supper.

25:06.880 --> 25:08.330
And Maggie's not family?

25:08.330 --> 25:10.920
Oh, please.
I didn't mean that.

25:10.920 --> 25:12.420
It's just -- [ Sighs ]

25:12.420 --> 25:15.460
Well, you could've
at least have called.

25:15.460 --> 25:17.290
Well, I like to keep
a sense of mystery.

25:17.290 --> 25:21.210
Oh, please. Are we talking
about Thomas Koracick now?

25:21.210 --> 25:24.250
Oh, we don't have to
talk about anything.

25:24.250 --> 25:26.290
Beautiful house.

25:26.290 --> 25:27.790
Oh, you've never been?

25:27.790 --> 25:29.960
I know. Sometimes
I think he worries

25:29.960 --> 25:32.420
about pushing
the dad angle.
Hmm.

25:32.420 --> 25:35.000
He's a good guy --
Richard.

25:35.000 --> 25:37.080
Very.
So is your mom.

25:37.080 --> 25:39.040
They are good people.

25:41.790 --> 25:43.170
Good folks.

25:45.500 --> 25:47.210
You want some wine?

25:47.210 --> 25:48.620
I would like
a gallon of it.

25:48.620 --> 25:51.080
I've been on this planet
for six decades.

25:51.080 --> 25:52.670
There have been penises
in my life

25:52.670 --> 25:54.750
that are not
attached to you.

25:54.750 --> 25:56.790
So stop trying
to change the subject.

25:56.790 --> 25:59.420
You haven't told me
what the subject is.

25:59.420 --> 26:03.500
I wanted to talk to Jackson
tonight alone, just us.

26:03.500 --> 26:04.710
Well, what about?

26:04.710 --> 26:06.380
The boy's grandfather
just passed!

26:06.380 --> 26:07.750
I understand that!

26:07.750 --> 26:09.420
[ Sighs ]
I'm sorry about all this.

26:09.420 --> 26:12.380
Oh, it's fine, it's fine.
My parents had loud discussions.

26:12.380 --> 26:13.920
Catherine:
It's complicated!

26:13.920 --> 26:17.420
I just -- I need to talk to
Jackson about his inheritance!

26:19.080 --> 26:20.620
You know what?
I'm just gonna -- Yeah.

26:20.620 --> 26:22.250
Richard:
How complicated is it?!

26:22.250 --> 26:24.710
Catherine: A quarter of a
billion dollars! That's how!

26:24.710 --> 26:29.420
♪♪

26:29.420 --> 26:31.750
Who's hungry?
[ Chuckles ]

26:31.750 --> 26:37.290
♪♪

26:37.290 --> 26:43.290
♪♪

26:50.540 --> 26:52.540
[ Silverware clinking ]

26:58.210 --> 27:00.460
Everything tastes
really wonderful.

27:00.460 --> 27:01.920
It's so wonderful.

27:07.580 --> 27:10.170
Tell me again why they
can't just give the
money to the foundation.

27:10.170 --> 27:11.790
He left plenty
to the foundation.

27:11.790 --> 27:13.290
That was his gift to you.

27:13.290 --> 27:15.330
That's not a gift, Mom.
It's an economy.

27:15.330 --> 27:17.170
It's how
he showed his love.

27:17.170 --> 27:19.380
Yeah, well,
I don't want it.

27:19.380 --> 27:21.170
You know what I do want?

27:21.170 --> 27:23.000
I want a fair chance to
actually win his damn award.

27:23.000 --> 27:24.540
Jackson.
I know.

27:24.540 --> 27:26.040
Look, I'm not complaining
about it. I just --

27:26.040 --> 27:28.710
Yes, you are.
And I will not abide it.

27:28.710 --> 27:30.750
I'm not complaining.
It's just -- It's a lot!

27:30.750 --> 27:32.420
You think having
a lot of money is tough?

27:32.420 --> 27:35.620
Try not having it
some time.

27:35.620 --> 27:39.170
No, I get it.
I mean, I --

27:39.170 --> 27:43.250
I, uh -- I went to college
on a full ride when I was 15,

27:43.250 --> 27:45.880
which sounds awesome,
but I had no friends

27:45.880 --> 27:47.960
and I cried all the time,
and it was awful.

27:47.960 --> 27:49.790
I mean, I don't know what
it's like to have Beyoncé money,

27:49.790 --> 27:52.000
but I do know
that research shows

27:52.000 --> 27:54.420
that having too many choices
is a leading cause of stress.

27:54.420 --> 27:56.960
And now Jackson can literally
choose to do anything

27:56.960 --> 27:59.000
for the rest of his life.

27:59.000 --> 28:01.670
You could buy a vineyard
and never work again.

28:01.670 --> 28:04.080
Or you could buy a hospital
and work until the day you die.

28:04.080 --> 28:05.420
Even if you give it away,

28:05.420 --> 28:07.750
you have to decide who gets it
and who doesn't.

28:07.750 --> 28:09.710
You could buy an island.

28:09.710 --> 28:11.580
Or you could buy two islands
and make them fight each other.

28:11.580 --> 28:13.250
I mean, I get that
you're not complaining.

28:13.250 --> 28:15.080
But it is a problem.
It is stressful.

28:15.080 --> 28:17.420
Still, it's a good problem
to have, right? [ Chuckles ]

28:20.710 --> 28:21.790
Is there more wine?

28:21.790 --> 28:23.790
[ Slurps ]

28:28.420 --> 28:31.210
-You know where you are?
-I'm at work.

28:31.210 --> 28:33.250
Do you know
who the president is?

28:33.250 --> 28:35.170
-I wish I didn't.
-Very good.

28:35.170 --> 28:38.710
Dr. Shepherd, your
post-op scans are pristine.

28:38.710 --> 28:40.250
I'm clearing you
to go home.

28:40.250 --> 28:42.000
I'll see you in a few days
for a follow-up, hmm?

28:42.000 --> 28:43.250
It's been a pleasure
being treated by me.

28:45.670 --> 28:48.170
Yay!
This is incredible!

28:48.170 --> 28:50.500
I want to see my scans.
All of them.

28:50.500 --> 28:52.960
Amelia,
he said you're fine.

28:52.960 --> 28:54.620
You're cleared
to go home.

28:54.620 --> 28:56.830
Something's wrong.
Something's missing.

28:56.830 --> 28:59.540
Um, please get my scans.

29:01.670 --> 29:03.960
Air Force,
with distinction,

29:03.960 --> 29:06.750
two tours in Iraq
in cybersecurity.

29:06.750 --> 29:08.000
Thank you for that.

29:08.000 --> 29:09.880
And you left
to go into medicine.

29:09.880 --> 29:11.290
One day I caught
some shrapnel,

29:11.290 --> 29:13.420
and I woke up on a cot
in a CSH tent.

29:13.420 --> 29:17.290
I watched 3 combat surgeons
save 37 soldiers in 6 hours.

29:17.290 --> 29:19.710
I counted.
I kept score.

29:19.710 --> 29:22.670
I thought, "That's not a bad way
to spend your time."

29:22.670 --> 29:24.540
Also, I watched a lot of
"M.A.S.H." when I was a kid,

29:24.540 --> 29:26.710
and I had a real thing
for Hawkeye Pierce.

29:26.710 --> 29:28.040
Me too!

29:29.120 --> 29:30.880
[ Chuckles ]

29:30.880 --> 29:34.210
I read all about the fire.
And the resident who set it?

29:34.210 --> 29:37.580
Incredible.
So smart, so brave.

29:37.580 --> 29:40.250
Just...fierce,
you know?

29:40.250 --> 29:42.540
She's officially
my new hero.

29:42.540 --> 29:45.040
And I'm so excited to see
all the changes you make
when you rebuild.

29:45.040 --> 29:47.620
We already rebuilt.

29:47.620 --> 29:51.000
Right! No. Of course you did.
It's...gorgeous!

29:51.000 --> 29:53.540
Who's your designer?

29:55.330 --> 29:57.580
Meredith: Come on, Nathan.
Come on, Nathan.

29:59.540 --> 30:01.540
Dr. Grey, uh,
if it's all right,

30:01.540 --> 30:03.710
um, I need you to take
my name off the paper.

30:03.710 --> 30:05.170
Why?

30:05.170 --> 30:08.380
It's okay. I know that
Alex told you about him.

30:08.380 --> 30:10.460
[ Gasps ]
Oh, Wilson, when I asked you

30:10.460 --> 30:12.460
for that picture,
I wasn't even thinking.

30:12.460 --> 30:14.000
It's not your job
to think about it.

30:14.000 --> 30:16.040
-It's okay.
-Okay.

30:20.210 --> 30:23.790
Why would you take your name
off that article?

30:23.790 --> 30:25.620
Because if I didn't,

30:25.620 --> 30:29.040
my psychopathic husband
might see my picture,

30:29.040 --> 30:31.080
learn my new name,
and come kill me.

30:31.080 --> 30:33.330
[ Laughs ] That's --

30:33.330 --> 30:35.040
Wait. Seriously?

30:35.040 --> 30:36.790
Y-You're married?

30:36.790 --> 30:38.170
And in hiding.

30:41.250 --> 30:43.620
Okay, how about you tell me
a secret about yourself

30:43.620 --> 30:48.040
so that I'm not the only one
who feels so horribly exposed?

30:48.040 --> 30:51.210
A-All right. Um...
[ Chuckles ]

30:51.210 --> 30:54.080
Uh, I'm training
for something,

30:54.080 --> 30:57.710
and if my wife finds out,
she is not gonna like it.

30:57.710 --> 30:59.920
Like, a lot.

31:02.420 --> 31:04.080
Wait. What is it?

31:06.000 --> 31:08.960
[ Scoffs ]

31:08.960 --> 31:11.750
I once had a patient
with bipolar disorder
and a malignant glioma.

31:11.750 --> 31:14.960
I took out the tumor.
Bipolar didn't change.
Shh.

31:14.960 --> 31:17.420
I once had a patient
with an armpit fetish pre-op.

31:17.420 --> 31:19.750
Tumor came out,
guy still loved him some pits.

31:19.750 --> 31:21.670
Are you saying
you think I'm nuts?

31:21.670 --> 31:23.540
I'm saying there's
nothing physically wrong

31:23.540 --> 31:25.620
with you anymore.
Go home.

31:27.710 --> 31:30.000
DeLuca, schedule
a functional MRI,

31:30.000 --> 31:32.830
a carotid duplex,
and another CT with contrast.

31:32.830 --> 31:34.500
Dr. Shepherd,
respectfully, I just --

31:34.500 --> 31:36.880
I don't understand
what we're looking for.

31:36.880 --> 31:38.790
I'll know when
I'm looking at it.

31:38.790 --> 31:41.120
♪ Leave the light on ♪

31:41.120 --> 31:43.210
♪ For myself when I come home ♪

31:43.210 --> 31:45.830
♪ Leave the light on ♪

31:45.830 --> 31:47.960
♪ For myself when I come home ♪

31:47.960 --> 31:50.290
♪ Leave the light on ♪

31:50.290 --> 31:53.040
♪ For myself when I come home ♪

31:53.040 --> 31:54.960
[ Cellphone chimes ]
♪ For myself when I come home ♪

31:54.960 --> 31:57.750
♪ For myself when I come home ♪

31:57.750 --> 32:00.000
♪ For myself when I come home ♪

32:00.000 --> 32:02.080
♪ For myself when I come home ♪

32:02.080 --> 32:03.710
♪ For myself when I come home ♪

32:03.710 --> 32:06.620
-You're the doctor?
-Yes. I'm Dr. Grey.

32:06.620 --> 32:09.210
What is the hold-up exactly
with my patient?

32:09.210 --> 32:11.880
The individual can't be
released until DHS comes

32:11.880 --> 32:14.000
and checks it off, and we're
waiting on some paperwork

32:14.000 --> 32:16.710
from INS that needs --
He cannot wait
for paperwork.

32:16.710 --> 32:19.250
Well, he seems all right for
now, so just let me do my job,

32:19.250 --> 32:21.210
and we'll get him out of here
as quick as we can.

32:21.210 --> 32:23.000
Does he?
Does he seem okay to you?

32:23.000 --> 32:24.710
Do you know what
thalassemia major looks like?

32:24.710 --> 32:26.250
Um...
I do.

32:26.250 --> 32:28.620
As clearly as the yellow
in your eyes tells me

32:28.620 --> 32:30.830
you should see a doctor
and get your liver checked soon.

32:30.830 --> 32:32.670
And do you have a form
that you fill out

32:32.670 --> 32:34.460
for standing by
while a child dies?

32:34.460 --> 32:37.080
Because you're gonna need that
one if you don't open this door

32:37.080 --> 32:39.960
and get me my patient
and let me do my job.

32:39.960 --> 32:42.750
♪ Leave the light on ♪

32:42.750 --> 32:45.670
♪ For myself when I come home ♪

32:45.670 --> 32:47.620
♪ Leave the light on ♪

32:47.620 --> 32:49.620
Hey.

32:49.620 --> 32:51.040
Hey.

32:51.040 --> 32:53.120
♪ Leave the light on ♪

32:53.120 --> 32:54.960
♪ For myself when I come home ♪

32:54.960 --> 32:56.500
♪ For myself when I come home ♪

33:04.460 --> 33:06.460
I never use lengthy medical
terms, always use first names.

33:06.460 --> 33:07.620
I try to
connect with them

33:07.620 --> 33:10.290
over an anecdote
or a shared experience.

33:10.290 --> 33:11.960
I think
patient connection

33:11.960 --> 33:15.670
is just as important
as surgical dexterity.

33:15.670 --> 33:18.920
Well, nobody ever bled out
from rudeness.

33:18.920 --> 33:21.580
Right. Right, right.

33:21.580 --> 33:23.830
Not as important.

33:25.960 --> 33:27.210
After I finished undergrad,

33:27.210 --> 33:29.580
I applied for the primary-care
rotation in Nepal.

33:29.580 --> 33:30.880
[ Dog yips ]

33:30.880 --> 33:32.710
[ Dog barking ]

33:35.250 --> 33:37.330
Why did you bring a dog
to your interview?

33:37.330 --> 33:38.880
Emotional support.

33:38.880 --> 33:41.040
And, legally, you're not
allowed to ask me that.

33:41.040 --> 33:43.790
[ Dog yips ]
Uh --

33:48.000 --> 33:50.290
[ Monitor beeping ]

33:50.290 --> 33:52.880
[ Indistinct conversations ]

33:52.880 --> 33:55.330
-Hey.
-Hey. Megan?

33:57.000 --> 33:58.750
Meredith:
I want you to stay calm.

33:58.750 --> 34:01.540
Don't make any sudden movements.
Don't jump out of bed.

34:01.540 --> 34:03.960
I don't want you
to ruin my work.

34:05.330 --> 34:06.330
What are you
doing here?

34:08.330 --> 34:09.880
I-I brought you
someone.

34:11.040 --> 34:12.540
Hi, Mama!

34:12.540 --> 34:15.000
Oh, my God!
[ Laughs ]

34:15.000 --> 34:16.790
[ Shrieking ]
Farouk! Oh, my God!

34:16.790 --> 34:18.710
Oh, my God!

34:20.500 --> 34:22.830
Oh, my God, oh, my God,
oh, my God!

34:22.830 --> 34:24.040
I missed you!

34:24.040 --> 34:25.000
I missed you, too!

34:25.000 --> 34:27.330
Ahh! [ Speaks Arabic ]

34:27.330 --> 34:29.120
[ Speaks Arabic ]

34:29.120 --> 34:32.120
Oh, my God. Are you real?
Are you real?

34:32.120 --> 34:34.170
[ Laughing ]
Are you really here?

34:34.170 --> 34:36.000
Ohh. This is
your Uncle Owen.

34:36.000 --> 34:38.750
-Owen, this is Farouk.
-Hey. Hey. How you doing?

34:38.750 --> 34:40.330
[ Laughter ]

34:40.330 --> 34:42.330
Thank you. Thank you
for looking after her.

34:42.330 --> 34:43.500
Thank you.

34:45.250 --> 34:48.460
[ Laughing ] Come here.
Oh, my God.

34:48.460 --> 34:51.670
[ Laughs ]
Have you eaten anything?

34:51.670 --> 34:53.750
You must be so tired.
Are you hungry?

34:53.750 --> 34:56.080
Farouk: I'm hungry.
The food here's terrible.

34:56.080 --> 34:58.420
[ Conversation continues
indistinctly ]

34:58.420 --> 35:00.250
[ Laughter ]

35:07.290 --> 35:10.500
I can't find the operative
report. Did Koracick dictate --

35:10.500 --> 35:12.420
I think I figured out
what you're looking for.

35:14.960 --> 35:16.960
It was this.

35:16.960 --> 35:18.670
This is what's missing.

35:24.420 --> 35:26.380
I think you've been waiting
for the other shoe to drop,

35:26.380 --> 35:29.380
for...something
to go wrong.

35:29.380 --> 35:32.960
And I think it might be
because, for years now,

35:32.960 --> 35:35.250
something was wrong.

35:35.250 --> 35:37.170
This thing was
growing inside of you,

35:37.170 --> 35:38.830
and you were
in constant danger.

35:38.830 --> 35:40.210
But now it's gone.

35:40.210 --> 35:43.250
And you're safe.

35:43.250 --> 35:45.540
And I think, for you,
that might feel...

35:47.540 --> 35:51.080
...like something's wrong,
but, uh...

35:53.120 --> 35:56.250
You know, I'm -- I'm sorry.
I thought I'd --

35:56.250 --> 36:01.620
♪♪

36:01.620 --> 36:03.290
[ Amelia breathes shakily ]

36:06.000 --> 36:08.830
[ Woman on P.A.
speaking indistinctly ]

36:08.830 --> 36:11.120
[ Elevator bell dings ]

36:16.420 --> 36:18.290
-Hey.
-Hi.

36:18.290 --> 36:19.830
Sorry again
about last night.

36:19.830 --> 36:22.250
Oh, please. I shouldn't
have had so much wine.

36:22.250 --> 36:24.830
No, no, no. I actually really
appreciated what you had to say.

36:24.830 --> 36:28.080
I appreciate, uh, you.

36:31.210 --> 36:32.960
I appreciate you, too.

36:34.620 --> 36:36.120
Hi, there.

36:36.120 --> 36:38.460
Hey. Hi. Thank you so much
for last night.

36:38.460 --> 36:42.080
Oh, Maggie,
I'm so glad you were there

36:42.080 --> 36:44.040
to talk some sense
into this one.

36:44.040 --> 36:45.460
He's pretty sensible,
I think.

36:45.460 --> 36:46.750
Oh, he's like me.

36:46.750 --> 36:49.380
My mom could talk to me
till she was blue in the face,

36:49.380 --> 36:51.540
but if my sister
told me something,

36:51.540 --> 36:54.000
I would actually listen.

36:54.000 --> 36:56.120
Let's do that again soon.

36:59.710 --> 37:02.170
-Have a good night, then.
-Yeah. You too.

37:06.000 --> 37:08.120
So, honey,
how's it going?

37:08.120 --> 37:10.120
Have you found all
your new interns yet?

37:10.120 --> 37:12.420
Well, the older I get,
the more I dislike them.

37:12.420 --> 37:14.080
[ Laughs ]

37:14.080 --> 37:17.580
Hey! Kit Cat!
You want to grab a drink?

37:17.580 --> 37:21.170
Um, we have plans,
uh, my wife and -- and I.

37:21.170 --> 37:23.120
We don't want
to miss our chance.

37:23.120 --> 37:24.460
I-I'm not gonna be here
much longer.

37:24.460 --> 37:26.460
Well, you have to
come around more often.

37:26.460 --> 37:29.540
Maybe you can do a lecture
a couple times a year, hmm?

37:29.540 --> 37:32.420
[ Laughing ] I'm gonna
make that happen. [ Laughs ]

37:32.420 --> 37:34.000
Mmm.

37:35.880 --> 37:38.170
Really? "Kit Cat"?

37:39.460 --> 37:42.380
You're that desperate
to see him again?

37:42.380 --> 37:45.790
Oh, honey, yes.
I like what he does to you.

37:45.790 --> 37:47.620
[ Groans ]

37:47.620 --> 37:49.210
[ Laughs ]

37:49.210 --> 37:53.040
[ Indistinct conversations ]

37:53.040 --> 37:55.420
Hey, so, I stocked the fridge
with all your favorites.

37:55.420 --> 37:57.750
I set the thermostat to boiling,
just how you like it.

37:57.750 --> 38:00.500
[ Exhales sharply ]
I want you to come home, Amelia.

38:02.620 --> 38:05.920
Yeah, I figured, um, you would
take care of your sister,

38:05.920 --> 38:09.790
and, uh, my sisters
would take care of me,

38:09.790 --> 38:11.170
and then --
And then what?

38:13.380 --> 38:16.120
And then I don't know.
And it's scary.

38:17.460 --> 38:19.790
[ Sighs ]

38:19.790 --> 38:22.790
You were coming to end it,
to leave me

38:22.790 --> 38:24.540
when I told you
that I was sick.

38:24.540 --> 38:26.420
Listen. I was upset.
But I didn't know --

38:26.420 --> 38:28.290
You were right.
I was awful to you.

38:28.290 --> 38:30.790
You were right
to want to leave.

38:30.790 --> 38:33.080
You had a tumor.

38:33.080 --> 38:35.290
-You married a tumor.
-I married you.

38:35.290 --> 38:36.880
We don't know
who that is anymore.

38:36.880 --> 38:38.670
I don't know who I am.

38:38.670 --> 38:41.920
So you don't
have to do this now.

38:41.920 --> 38:44.500
You can be free.

38:46.620 --> 38:50.540
♪ Say everything's better
in the daylight ♪

38:50.540 --> 38:52.330
Amelia.

38:52.330 --> 38:55.290
♪ So why'd you leave me
in the dark? ♪

38:55.290 --> 38:57.380
You're my wife, okay?

38:57.380 --> 38:58.920
In sickness
and in health.

38:58.920 --> 39:00.710
Come home.

39:00.710 --> 39:02.420
Amelia:
The trouble with crossed wires

39:02.420 --> 39:05.670
is you don't know they happened
until it's too late.

39:05.670 --> 39:08.540
So we have to be very careful
with our connections.

39:08.540 --> 39:10.290
Thank you.

39:10.290 --> 39:11.920
♪ And when you told me
what I wanna hear ♪

39:11.920 --> 39:13.330
[ Exhales sharply ]

39:13.330 --> 39:16.460
♪ Don't just say nothing,
say nothing ♪

39:16.460 --> 39:20.170
They take time, care,
and attention.

39:20.170 --> 39:22.040
Rounds don't start
that early.

39:22.040 --> 39:24.290
I'm trying to
get in a run.

39:24.290 --> 39:25.960
You've been
running a lot lately.

39:25.960 --> 39:27.830
♪ I believe ♪

39:27.830 --> 39:29.170
I'm just
staying in shape.

39:29.170 --> 39:30.880
[ Sighs ]

39:30.880 --> 39:33.040
♪ Now I see ♪

39:33.040 --> 39:34.330
What, you, uh...

39:34.330 --> 39:35.750
♪ You're only gonna
break me down ♪

39:35.750 --> 39:38.750
You don't want me
to stay in shape?

39:38.750 --> 39:41.210
